column191: participantComments:"I responded the way I did because in all but the last round both farmers worked together in what seemed to be agreement to take the quickest route to the center tree so they could both get the most benefit from working together. Then the last round
column192: the purple farmer betrayed the yellow farmer and made a profit while gving the other a loss while harvesting a corner tree on his own. I would hope he felt guilty about that and the yellow farmer would feel angry"
